data.value: Identity value generation cannot be used for the property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' because the property type is '{propertyType}'. Identity value generation can only be used with signed integer properties.

data.name: IncludePropertyDuplicated
data.value: The include property '{entityType}.{property}' was specified multiple times for the index {index}.

data.name: IncludePropertyNotFound

data.name: IncompatibleSqlOutputClauseMismatch
data.value: Cannot use table '{table}' for entity type '{entityType}' since it is being used for entity type '{otherEntityType}' and entity type '{entityTypeWithSqlOutputClause}' is configured to use the SQL OUTPUT clause, but entity type '{entityTypeWithoutSqlOutputClause}' is not.

data.name: IncompatibleTableMemoryOptimizedMismatch
data.value: Cannot use table '{table}' for entity type '{entityType}' since it is being used for entity type '{otherEntityType}' and entity type '{memoryOptimizedEntityType}' is marked as memory-optimized, but entity type '{nonMemoryOptimizedEntityType}' is not.

data.name: IndexTableRequired
data.value: SQL Server requires the table name to be specified for index operations. Specify table name in calls to 'MigrationBuilder.RenameIndex' and 'DropIndex'.

data.name: InvalidColumnNameForFreeText
data.value: The expression passed to the 'propertyReference' parameter of the 'FreeText' method is not a valid reference to a property. The expression must represent a reference to a full-text indexed property on the object referenced in the from clause: 'from e in context.Entities where EF.Functions.FreeText(e.SomeProperty, textToSearchFor) select e'

data.name: InvalidTableToIncludeInScaffolding
data.value: The specified table '{table}' is not in a valid format. Specify tables using the format '[schema].[table]'.

data.name: JsonValuePathExpressionsNotSupported
data.value: A non-constant array index or property name was used when navigating inside a JSON document, but EF Core's SQL Server compatibility level is set to {compatibilityLevel}; this is only supported with compatibility level 140 (SQL Server 2017) or higher.

data.name: LeastGreatestCompatibilityLevelTooLow
data.value: This usage of Math.Min or Math.Max requires SQL Server functions LEAST and GREATEST, which require compatibility level 160.

data.name: LogByteIdentityColumn
data.value: The property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' is of type 'byte', but is set up to use a SQL Server identity column; this requires that values starting at 255 and counting down will be used for temporary key values. A temporary key value is needed for every entity inserted in a single call to 'SaveChanges'. Care must be taken that these values do not collide with real key values.

data.name: LogColumnWithoutType
data.value: A database type for column '{columnName}' on table '{tableName}' could not be found, the column will be skipped.

data.name: LogConflictingValueGenerationStrategies
data.value: Both the SqlServerValueGenerationStrategy '{generationStrategy}' and '{otherGenerationStrategy}' have been set on property '{propertyName}' on entity type '{entityName}'. Configuring two strategies is usually unintentional and will likely result in a database error.

data.name: LogDecimalTypeKey
data.value: The decimal property '{property}' is part of a key on entity type '{entityType}'. If the configured precision and scale don't match the column type in the database, this will cause values to be silently truncated if they do not fit in the default precision and scale. Consider using a different property as the key, or make sure that the database column type matches the model configuration and enable decimal rounding warnings using 'SET NUMERIC_ROUNDABORT ON'.

data.name: LogDefaultDecimalTypeColumn
data.value: No store type was specified for the decimal property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}'. This will cause values to be silently truncated if they do not fit in the default precision and scale. Explicitly specify the SQL server column type that can accommodate all the values in 'OnModelCreating' using 'HasColumnType', specify precision and scale using 'HasPrecision', or configure a value converter using 'HasConversion'.

data.name: LogDuplicateForeignKeyConstraintIgnored
data.value: Skipping foreign key '{foreignKeyName}' on table '{tableName}' since it is a duplicate of '{duplicateForeignKeyName}'.

data.value: Found column with table: {tableName}, column name: {columnName}, ordinal: {ordinal}, data type: {dataType}, maximum length: {maxLength}, precision: {precision}, scale: {scale}, nullable: {nullable}, identity: {identity}, default value: {defaultValue}, computed value: {computedValue}, computed value is stored: {stored}.

data.value: Unable to find a table in the database matching the selected table '{table}'.

data.name: LogMissingViewDefinitionRights
data.value: The database user has not been granted 'VIEW DEFINITION' rights. Scaffolding requires these rights to construct the Entity Framework model correctly. Without these rights, parts of the scaffolded model may be missing, resulting in incorrect interactions between Entity Framework and the database at runtime.

data.name: LogPrincipalColumnNotFound
data.value: Skipping foreign key with identity '{id}' on table '{tableName}', since the principal column '{principalColumnName}' on the foreign key's principal table, '{principalTableName}', was not found in the model.

data.name: LogPrincipalTableInformationNotFound
data.value: Skipping foreign key '{foreignKeyName}' on table '{tableName}' since principal table information is not available. This usually happens when the user doesn't have permission to read data about principal table.

data.name: LogPrincipalTableNotInSelectionSet
data.value: Skipping foreign key '{foreignKeyName}' on table '{tableName}' since principal table '{principalTableName}' was not found in the model. This usually happens when the principal table was not included in the selection set.

data.name: LogReflexiveConstraintIgnored
data.value: Skipping foreign key '{foreignKeyName}' on table '{tableName}' since all of its columns reference themselves.

data.name: LogSavepointsDisabledBecauseOfMARS
data.value: Savepoints are disabled because Multiple Active Result Sets (MARS) is enabled. If 'SaveChanges' fails, then the transaction cannot be automatically rolled back to a known clean state. Instead, the transaction should be rolled back by the application before retrying 'SaveChanges'. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2149338 for more information and examples. To identify the code which triggers this warning, call 'ConfigureWarnings(w => w.Throw(SqlServerEventId.SavepointsDisabledBecauseOfMARS))'.

data.name: MultipleIdentityColumns
data.value: The properties {properties} are configured to use 'Identity' value generation and are mapped to the same table '{table}', but only one column per table can be configured as 'Identity'. Call 'ValueGeneratedNever' in 'OnModelCreating' for properties that should not use 'Identity'.

data.name: NoInitialCatalog
data.value: The database name could not be determined. To use 'EnsureDeleted', the connection string must specify 'Initial Catalog'.

data.name: NoSavepointRelease
data.value: SQL Server does not support releasing a savepoint.

data.name: QueryingOrderedBinaryJsonCollectionsNotSupported
data.value: The query is attempting to query a JSON collection of binary data in a context that requires preserving the ordering of the collection; this isn't supported by SQL Server.

data.name: SaveChangesFailedBecauseOfComputedColumnWithFunction
data.value: Could not save changes because the target table has computed column with a function that performs data access. Please configure your table accordingly, see https://aka.ms/efcore-docs-sqlserver-save-changes-and-output-clause for more information.

data.name: SaveChangesFailedBecauseOfTriggers
data.value: Could not save changes because the target table has database triggers. Please configure your table accordingly, see https://aka.ms/efcore-docs-sqlserver-save-changes-and-output-clause for more information.

data.name: SequenceBadType
data.value: SQL Server sequences cannot be used to generate values for the property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' because the property type is '{propertyType}'. Sequences can only be used with integer properties.

data.name: SplitQueryOffsetWithoutOrderBy
data.value: The query uses 'Skip' without specifying ordering and uses split query mode. This generates incorrect results. Either provide ordering or run query in single query mode using `AsSingleQuery()`. See https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2196526 for more information.

data.name: TemporalAllEntitiesMappedToSameTableMustBeTemporal
data.value: Entity type '{entityType}' should be marked as temporal because it shares table mapping with another entity that has been marked as temporal. Alternatively, other entity types that share the same table must be non-temporal.

data.name: TemporalExpectedPeriodPropertyNotFound
data.value: Entity type '{entityType}' mapped to temporal table does not contain the expected period property: '{propertyName}'.

data.name: TemporalMigrationModifyingComputedColumnNotSupported
data.value: Modifying SQL of a computed column '{columnName}' on a temporal table '{tableName}' is not supported by migrations.

data.name: TemporalMustDefinePeriodProperties
data.value: Entity type '{entityType}' mapped to temporal table must have a period start and a period end property.

data.name: TemporalNavigationExpansionBetweenTemporalAndNonTemporal
data.value: Temporal query is trying to use navigation to an entity '{entityType}' which itself doesn't map to temporal table. Either map the entity to temporal table or use join manually to access it.

data.name: TemporalNavigationExpansionOnlySupportedForAsOf
data.value: Navigation expansion is only supported for '{operationName}' temporal operation. For other operations use join manually.

data.name: TemporalNotSupportedForTableSplittingWithInconsistentPeriodMapping
data.value: When multiple temporal entities are mapped to the same table, their period {periodType} properties must map to the same column. Issue happens for entity type '{entityType}' with period property '{periodProperty}' which is mapped to column '{periodColumn}'. Expected period column name is '{expectedColumnName}'.

data.name: TemporalOnlyOnRoot
data.value: Only root entity type should be marked as temporal. Entity type: '{entityType}'.

data.name: TemporalOnlySupportedForTPH
data.value: Temporal tables are only supported for entities using Table-Per-Hierarchy inheritance mapping. Entity type: '{entityType}'.

data.name: TemporalPeriodPropertyCantHaveDefaultValue
data.value: Period property '{entityType}.{propertyName}' can't have a default value specified.

data.name: TemporalPeriodPropertyMustBeInShadowState
data.value: Period property '{entityType}.{propertyName}' must be a shadow property.

data.name: TemporalPeriodPropertyMustBeMappedToDatetime2
data.value: Period property '{entityType}.{propertyName}' must be mapped to a column of type '{columnType}'.

data.name: TemporalPeriodPropertyMustBeNonNullableDateTime
data.value: Period property '{entityType}.{propertyName}' must be non-nullable and of type '{dateTimeType}'.

data.name: TemporalPropertyMappedToPeriodColumnMustBeValueGeneratedOnAddOrUpdate
data.value: Property '{entityType}.{propertyName}' is mapped to the period column and must have ValueGenerated set to '{valueGeneratedValue}'.

data.name: TemporalSetOperationOnMismatchedSources
data.value: Set operation can't be applied on entity '{entityType}' because temporal operations on both arguments don't match.

data.name: TransientExceptionDetected
data.value: An exception has been raised that is likely due to a transient failure. Consider enabling transient error resiliency by adding 'EnableRetryOnFailure' to the 'UseSqlServer' call.
